---
description: When raising a PR for a Notion task, add the PR link, deployment link, and summary as a comment on the card
alwaysApply: true
---

# Notion + PR Workflow

When you raise a PR for a task that was **fetched from Notion** (e.g. from a Launch Board card, database page, or any Notion task the user referenced):

1. **Create the PR** via the GitHub MCP. If the GitHub MCP fails, fall back to the local GitHub CLI (`gh pr create`). **Important:** Before using the CLI, run `gh auth status` — if the logged-in user is "KarimtamerBW", do **not** create the PR via CLI; inform the user they need to switch accounts or use the GitHub MCP.
2. **If the card was in the "In Progress" column**, move it to the "To Be Reviewed" column on the same board. Use `notion-update-page` with `command: "update_properties"` and set the status property to "To Be Reviewed" (fetch the database schema first to get the exact property name).
3. **Add a comment to the Notion card** — do **not** put the PR link in the Notes property. Use the `notion-create-comment` tool with:
   - `page_id`: The Notion page ID from the task (from its URL or fetch result).
   - `rich_text`: A comment containing:
     - The PR link (as clickable text, e.g. "PR #3" with the GitHub URL).
     - The deployment/preview link (e.g. Vercel preview URL from GitHub status checks or the user).
     - A brief summary of what was done (commits, main changes, or key fixes).

**Example comment structure:**
```
PR: [PR #3](https://github.com/owner/repo/pull/3)

Deployment: [Preview](https://project-git-branch-team.vercel.app)

Summary: Fixed POST /sellers entry point for production, removed blocking createIndex, added request logging.
```

**How to get the deployment link:** Check GitHub commit statuses for the branch (Vercel posts deployment URLs there), or use the URL format `https://<project>-git-<branch>-<scope>.vercel.app`. If the user provides a deployment URL from the Vercel dashboard, use that.

**How to format the link in rich_text:**
```json
[
  { "type": "text", "text": { "content": "PR: " } },
  { "type": "text", "text": { "content": "PR #3", "link": { "url": "https://github.com/owner/repo/pull/3" } } },
  { "type": "text", "text": { "content": "\n\nDeployment: " } },
  { "type": "text", "text": { "content": "Preview", "link": { "url": "https://project-git-branch.vercel.app" } } },
  { "type": "text", "text": { "content": "\n\nSummary: <brief description of changes>" } }
]
```

**When this applies:** Only when the user explicitly asks to "raise a PR" (or similar) for a task that you previously fetched from Notion. If the task came from elsewhere or the Notion page ID is unknown, skip the comment step.
